<h2 id="1-antimasklaw">1. #AntiMaskLaw</h2>

<p><img src="http://localhost:4000/notes/assets/antimask.png" /></p>

<p>Projects a different face on top of your face. It surfaced on Twitter from the account of an Hong Kong protester, without any informations on the tweet.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Wearable face projector #AntiMaskLaw #EmergencyLaw</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Didnâ€™t dig further, in respect of clandestine feeling intended by the poster. But I dig the idea, so it made it into the findings.</p>

<p><a href="https://twitter.com/HappySharingDay/status/1180154863637819393?s=20">here</a></p>

<h2 id="2-exausting-a-crowd-2015">2. Exausting a Crowd (2015)</h2>

<p><img src="http://localhost:4000/notes/assets/exausting.png" /></p>

<p>A website playing a 12 hour video from a London (and other cities location). At any time you can zoom-in in a specific part of the scene, for instance at a person, and add a comment.</p>

<p>Very nice project by Kyle Mcdonald from 2015. I somehow missed then, just got to my attention as it was recently updated with a new location in Beijing.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.exhaustingacrowd.com/beijing">here</a></p>

<h2 id="3-amazon-echo-loop">3. Amazon Echo Loop</h2>

<p><img src="http://localhost:4000/notes/assets/echoloop.png" /></p>

<p>You cup your hand, whisper some question onto it, bring the hand to your ear and listen to the response. As part of a pilot/beta program, Amazon released an Alexa ring and Alexa glasses. Iâ€™m looking forward to more wearable pieces with voice assistant like these.</p>

